article.description: Antonio Jenifer sank two free throws and then added a dunk to help St. Francis Brooklyn close out the regular season with four straight wins and a 55-49 defeat of Mount St. Mary's on Saturday.
article.headline: Jenifer dunk caps St. Francis Brooklyn's 55-49 win
article.linkText: Jenifer dunk caps St. Francis Brooklyn's 55-49 win
article.story: NEW YORK -- Antonio Jenifer sank two free throws and then added a dunk to help St. Francis Brooklyn close out the regular season with four straight wins and a 55-49 defeat of Mount St. Mary's on Saturday. Jenifer also grabbed 13 rebounds in the tight, low-scoring game. Yunus Hopkinson added 12 points and Amdy Fall had 10 points and nine rebounds for the Terriers (15-16, 11-7 Northeast Conference). St. Francis built a late six-point lead on a Fall jumper, but BK Ashe sliced it to 49-47 with a layup with 2:43 left. Tyreek Jewell dunked for St. Francis and, in the final 45 seconds, Jenifer scored his final four points. Freshman Elijah Long scored 16 -- coming within four of his career best -- to lead Mount St. Mary's (13-18, 10-8), Ashe added 10. St. Francis earned the no. 4 seed to the NEC tourney and will host fifth-seeded Mount St. Mary's on Wednesday.
